<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[840,1478,1313,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,1003,1569,1588]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[1027,1162,1567,1589]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sousae">
<emphasis box="[1027,1162,1567,1589]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Solanum sousae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from southern Mexico in the states of Puebla and Oaxaca, in mesophyllous forests and oak-pine- 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1152,1624,1645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Altingiaceae" genus="Liquidambar" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1152,1624,1645]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Liquidambar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forests on steep slopes with rich soils, from 
<quantity box="[948,1086,1652,1674]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="m" value="1750.0" valueMax="1900.0" valueMin="1600.0">1600–1900 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[840,1478,1313,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,984,1682,1701]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[1008,1144,1680,1702]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sousae">
<emphasis box="[1008,1144,1680,1702]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Solanum sousae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named in honour of Mario Sousa Sánchez (MEXU), whose dedication to the advance of knowledge of the Mexican flora has resulted in a whole new generation of Mexican botanists.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="6.[840,1478,1313,1956]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,1222,1794,1814]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Preliminary conservation status.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Knapp" authorityYear="2010" box="[1246,1379,1793,1815]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sousae">
<emphasis box="[1246,1379,1793,1815]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Solanum sousae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from only three widely dispersed collections, none of which falls within a protected area. It must be considered at threat, but further collecting and observation are a priority.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
